ttps://github.com/kesslerio/attio-mcp-server/actions/runs/16606935114)\\n\\n---\\n### Analysis Complete: Issue #365 get-company-notes field structure mismatch\\n\\n#### Todo List:\\n- [x] Read current company notes formatter implementation\\n- [x] Review test file to understand expected field structures  \\n- [x] Check person notes formatter for similar issues\\n- [x] Examine API operations and type definitions\\n- [x] Analyze the proposed solution approach\\n- [x] Provide comprehensive technical feedback\\n\\n### Analysis Results\\n\\n#### Issue Confirmed \u2705\\n\\nThe issue analysis is **accurate**. I've identified several key problems:\\n\\n1. **Root Cause Validated**: \\n   - `src/handlers/tool-configs/companies/notes.ts:32` only checks `note.content || ''`  \\n   - `src/handlers/tool-configs/people/notes.ts:25` has the **same issue** - only checks `note.content`\\n\\n2. **Test File Shows the Solution**: \\n   - `test/handlers/tool-configs/companies/notes.test.ts:19-24` demonstrates the correct approach:\\n   ```typescript\\n   const content =\\n     note.content ||\\n     note.data?.content ||\\n     note.values?.content ||\\n     note.text ||\\n     note.body;\\n   ```\\n\\n3. **Both Notes Types Affected**: Person notes formatter has identical issue - affects entire notes system\\n\\n#### Technical Assessment\\n\\n**Proposed Solution is Sound** \u2705\\nThe multi-field fallback approach in the issue description matches exactly what the test file demonstrates. This pattern handles:\\n- Standard API responses (`note.content`)\\n- Nested data structures (`note.data?.content`, `note.values?.content`) \\n- Alternative field names (`note.text`, `note.body`)\\n\\n**Type Mismatch Identified** \u26a0\ufe0f\\n- `src/types/attio.ts:220` defines `AttioNote.content: string` as direct property\\n- But actual API responses apparently use nested/alternative structures\\n- Type definition may need updating to reflect reality\\n\\n**Debug Infrastructure Already Exists** \u2705\\nCompany notes formatter already has debug logging (lines 21-26, 36-46) that would help identify actual API response structure.\\n\\n#### Recommended Implementation Approach\\n\\n1. **Update both formatters** (companies + people) with identical multi-field logic\\n2. **Add debug logging** to person notes formatter to match company notes\\n3. **Consider updating AttioNote interface** to reflect actual API response variations\\n4. **Test with actual API responses** to confirm which fields are being used\\n\\n#### Impact Assessment\\n\\n**Critical Issue** - This breaks core CRM functionality. Users cannot see note content, making the notes tools essentially useless for their primary purpose.\\n\\nThe proposed solution is technically sound and follows the pattern already established in the test file. Implementation should be straightforward.\\n\\n---\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"claude[bot]\",\"id\":209825114,\"node_id\":\"BOT_kgDODIGtWg\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/in/1236702?v=4\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/apps/claude\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"type\":\"Bot\",\"site_admin\":false,\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/claude%5Bbot%5D\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/claude%5Bbot%5D/events{/privacy}\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/claude%5Bbot%5D/following{/other_user}\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/claude%5Bbot%5D/followers\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/claude%5Bbot%5D/gists{/gist_id}\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/claude%5Bbot%5D/orgs\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/claude%5Bbot%5D/received_events\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/claude%5Bbot%5D/repos\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/claude%5Bbot%5D/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/claude%5Bbot%5D/subscriptions\"},\"reactions\":{\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"confused\":0,\"h